    </div> 
    <figcaption>Sen Ê£Æ. Âπ≥Â∏∏ÂøÉ (piÃÅng chaÃÅng xiÃÑn). Translation: peace of mind, one's natural self, an unagitated mind. Linocut on paper. 2019. Composed in the style of thangka paintings that traditionally depict the Buddha, the dragon curled behing the halo represents the possible threats to one's peace of mind.</figcaption>
